{{for|the village in Meyaneh County|Varzeqan, Meyaneh}} {{Infobox settlement |official_name =Varzaqan |native_name = ورزقان |settlement_type = City |image_skyline =Gol-Akhoor waterfall.JPG |imagesize = |image_caption = Gol Akhur waterfall |pushpin_map =Iran |mapsize =150px |subdivision_type = [[List of countries|Country]] |subdivision_name = {{flag|Iran}} |subdivision_type1 =[[Provinces of Iran|Province]] |subdivision_name1 =[[East Azerbaijan Province|East Azerbaijan]] |subdivision_type2 =[[Counties of Iran|County]] |subdivision_name2 =[[Varzaqan County|Varzaqan]] |subdivision_type3 =[[Bakhsh]] |subdivision_name3 =[[Central District (Varzaqan County)|Central]] |leader_title = |leader_name = |established_title = |established_date = |area_total_km2 = |area_footnotes = |population_as_of = 2016 Census |population_total =5,348 <ref>https://www.amar.org.ir/english</ref> |population_density_km2 =auto |timezone = [[Iran Standard Time|IRST]] |utc_offset = +3:30 |timezone_DST = [[Iran Daylight Time|IRDT]] |utc_offset_DST = +4:30 |coordinates = {{coord|38|30|35|N|46|39|16|E|region:IR|display=inline,title}} |elevation_m = |website = www.varzeqan.com |area_code = |footnotes = }} '''Varzaqan''' ({{lang-fa|ورزقان}}; also [[Romanize]]d as '''Varzeqān''' and '''Warzagan'''; formerly, '''Karzigan''' (Persian: كَرزيگَن), also Romanized as '''Kārzigān''' and '''Karzygan''')<ref>{{GEOnet3|-3088233}}</ref> is a city & capital of [[Varzaqan County]], [[East Azerbaijan Province]], [[Iran]]. At the 2006 census, its population was 3,549, in 930 families.<ref>{{IranCensus2006|03}}</ref> The city is famous for the [[Sungun copper mine]], 25&nbsp;km from the city centre, which is estimated to have 3 percent of the known copper reserves in the world.
==Historical landmark== The [[cuneiform]] inscription in the village of [[Saqandel]] is the most famous historical monument in the region.
==Earthquakes== {{main|2012 East Azerbaijan earthquakes}}
The area is subject to earthquakes, and in 2012 a number of people were killed when an [[earthquake doublet]] (magnitude 6.4 and 6.3) struck on the afternoon of 11 August.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Iran earthquake relief efforts begin after 250 killed|date=12 August 2012 |newspaper=BBC News|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-19231118}}</ref>
==Economy== Farming is the predominant occupation in the rural areas. The area produces apple, pear, cherry, walnut and apricot fruit. Recently spruce trees have been planted as the start of a forestry industry. Cold water fish farming has been started.<ref name="Arzyl">{{Cite web|author=Arzyl, Ahmed Hassan Nejad ( احمد حسن نژاد ارزیل)|year=2010|title=تاریخچه شهرستان ورزقان (History of Varzeqan)|url=http://varzegan.ershad-as.ir/?PageID=16|access-date=2012-08-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120821155933/http://varzegan.ershad-as.ir/?PageID=16|archive-date=2012-08-21|url-status=dead}}</ref>
Varzeqan is a mining centre for base metal mining, as well as gold. The Sungun copper mine is now the largest copper mine in northwestern Iran. The deposit itself is one of the largest copper deposits in the world. There are nearby gold mines at Shrfabad, Hyzjan, Tshkhsrv, Astrgan, [[Andaryan gold mine|Andryan]] and Myvhrvd.<ref name="Arzyl" />
